parcel.name: House du Perlin Sur L'eau by Elated Pixel

features.text: I spend a considerable portion of my time fine-tuning probability distributions to achieve the desired aesthetic effects. - Tyler Hobbs

Much of our lives are spent in programmed software environments...shaping our relationships, our communication, our consumption, our creation, our learning and memory, our very view of ourselves. - Tyler Hobbs

House du Perlin Sur Leau means Perlin House on the Water. Perlin House was largely improvised around the basic concept of a large fish tank underneath a glass ground floor. And thats where perlin (math structures) came in: its ideal for faux undersea shapes. Then I thought it would be interesting to have those shapes come up from under the 1st floor and envelope the house, being visible yet largely out of the way. It worked. Perlin Beach and the front + inside steps + banisters were made after. Interestingly, the decorative jagged b/w boundary around the building was the first thing Id put down more than a year ago when I decided to make the parcel into a park (changing my mind months later due to inexperience at foliage-making). I knew it was going to be a public place, but the purpose of Perlin House was clear after I put up a Tyler Hobbs practice piece (literally) as a placeholder. One Hobbs practice piece turned into two, then three so that most of the 2nd floor artwork of Perlin House is lesser-known works by Tyler, who Ive met in NYC and subsequently interviewed on Twitter Spaces. So there you have it. Enjoy House du Perlin Sur Leau! - Elated Pixel, Jan 2023
